   "id": "T33",
   "title": "Survivor NPCs — encounterable people with state & needs",
   "milestone": "M3",
   "status": "done",
   "note": "Done 2026-07-06 (M3 Part 1): NPCState + GameState.npcs; SAVE_SCHEMA_VERSION 4->5 with one forward-only rung migrateV4toV5 (seeds npcs:{}). content/npcs + npc.schema.json (schema-first; gate now 18 entries/6 types) — Sarah/Marcus/Ruth. Deterministic spawn from a new named `npc` RNG stream (spawnNpcs in startRun); needs drift via the T22 economy wired at pipeline stage 5 (updateCompanions body; 14-stage order unchanged); npcs added to TRACKED_SYSTEMS. Verified: engine 265 (+26) green, save-lossless, v4->v5 migration, 40-turn Rivermouth golden run byte-identical with 0 no-op turns and survivors persisted+simulated. FR-NPC-01 (VS subset)."
  },
  {
   "id": "T34",
   "title": "Trust & disposition model",
   "milestone": "M3",
   "status": "done",
   "note": "Done 2026-07-06 (M3 Part 1): src/sim/trust.ts — trust 0-100 on NPCState seeded from disposition (DISPOSITION_TRUST); asymmetric action deltas (help +15/share +10/trade +5; threaten -20/rob -30/abandon -25) via applyTrustEvent; adjustTrust clamps; trustTier bands + canParley (>=20) / canRecruit (>=70) gates feeding T35/T36. No free regen — trust never drifts, a betrayal sticks (property test + end-to-end). Pure/integer, save-lossless. FR-NPC-02 (VS subset)."
  },
  {
   "id": "T35",
   "title": "Dialogue & interaction choices",
   "milestone": "M3",
   "status": "todo",
   "note": "FR-NPC-03: meeting a survivor offers talk/trade/help/threaten as Scene choices with known costs and hidden outcomes (no fake choices), engine-resolved and client-narrated. Every option debits a real resource (time/trust/loot). Surfaced accessibly per the T19/T20 UI contract."
  },
  {
   "id": "T36",
   "title": "Companion recruitment",
   "milestone": "M3",
   "status": "todo",
   "note": "FR-NPC-04: a sufficiently-trusted survivor can join the run as a companion (party state carried across turns and saves). Extra hands AND an extra mouth — contributes to search/defence, consumes food/water — a real trade, not a free buff. Save-lossless across recruit/lose."
  },
  {
   "id": "T37",
   "title": "Claim a shelter",
   "milestone": "M3",
   "status": "todo",
   "note": "FR-SHL-01: claim a discovered node as a base — a safety bonus (lower night threat / better rest quality), one active shelter per run, in GameState (schema rung if needed). The first place on the map that is yours; anchors T38/T39."
  },
  {
   "id": "T38",
   "title": "Fortify & upkeep",
   "milestone": "M3",
   "status": "todo",
   "note": "FR-SHL-02: spend loot + time to fortify the shelter (dampen node noise, resist horde drift, raise the detection floor against night hunters); fortification decays and needs upkeep — a live maintenance decision against the reactive world, not a one-time purchase."
  },
  {
   "id": "T39",
   "title": "Shared stash",
   "milestone": "M3",
   "status": "todo",
   "note": "FR-SHL-03 / FR-PLR-04: deposit/withdraw loot at the shelter, a store separate from the T18 carry budget so a run can bank surplus. Depletion/theft hooks to the contested world (a raided stash is a story beat). Save-lossless; weight still bites on the road."
  },
  {
   "id": "T40",
   "title": "First authored story arc",
   "milestone": "M3",
   "status": "todo",
   "note": "FR-STORY-01: one scripted multi-beat arc as a deterministic trigger chain over the sim (a survivor in trouble -> a costed choice -> a consequence that ripples into trust/shelter/world). Append-only into Living History (T31); save-lossless; reproducible from a seed. Proof that systems can carry a story."
  },
  {
   "id": "T41",
   "title": "Story surfaced in the Scene",
   "milestone": "M3",
   "status": "todo",
   "note": "FR-UI-STORY: narrative beats and NPC/story leads appear in the Four-Questions UI alongside the world-surfacing pass (weather/threat/horde), plain-text and keyboard-only (NFR-ACC). A run should READ as a story, not a stat sheet — the perceivable half of the M3 fun-gate."
  },
  {
   "id": "T42",
   "title": "Slice Fun Gate",
   "milestone": "M3",
   "status": "todo",
   "note": "PRODUCTION §4 Stage-2 — the owner's human verdict that 'a run becomes a story'. The M3 exit; cannot be auto-passed. Record it in the Fun-Gate log; retires the 'systemic but not fun' risk. A pass opens M4 (content-complete city); a fail freezes content and re-invests in people/shelter/story."
  }
 ],
